<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Product Design on RaihnForge</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/tags/product-design/</link><description>Recent content in Product Design on RaihnForge</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2014 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/tags/product-design/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Keyes Possibilities</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/keyes-possibilities/</link><pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2014 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/keyes-possibilities/</guid><description>&lt;p>This Spring, 2014 a few family member of mine dedicated themselves to be apart of a triathlon.  They decided to make motivational family Keyes Jerseys.  I was called into action in effort to make this a reality.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/keyesLogoSM.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/keyesLogoSM.png" alt="keyesLogoSM" title="keyesLogoSM">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/keyesLogoJerseyDemo.png">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/keyesLogoJerseyDemo.png" alt="keyesLogoJerseyDemo" title="keyesLogoJerseyDemo">&lt;/a> The keys’ esthetic was a bit on the ‘techy’ side, but I’d been deep into my game project when I designed them, so some of the content philosophy bled over.  The intent was to ensure that each key was interesting, being that they are blown up about tens times larger than an actual key would be.  I enjoyed the the challenge of making print quality interesting compositions out of enlarged every day objects. Though, the hurtle and real life issues made the project more of an obstacle than it should have, I did quite enjoy the result.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Christmas Card</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/christmas-card/</link><pubDate>Wed, 31 Oct 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/christmas-card/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Christmas-Card_7A9C/holiday-greeting-card.png">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Christmas-Card_7A9C/holiday-greeting-card_thumb.png" alt="holiday-greeting-card" title="holiday-greeting-card">&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I found this Christmas Card I designed. My wife and I sent these out a couple of years ago. I love Christmas time and it was really great to pass out personalized cards to my friends and family. Maybe I can find the time to make another this year. If you like it, feel free to download the file, print at home, and fold your way to fun! &lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Christmas-Card_7A9C/wlEmoticon-openmouthedsmile.png" alt="Open-mouthed smile">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Overlay for X-Com Stream</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/overlay-for-x-com-stream/</link><pubDate>Fri, 24 Aug 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/overlay-for-x-com-stream/</guid><description>&lt;p>A couple of weeks ago a friend of mine, Kayfix, and I decided to play a run through of X-Com with &amp;ldquo;Field Expedient Multiplayer.&amp;rdquo; The idea is that we run with two teams of four, and that all deaths are permanent (as stated in our code of conduct) and that we cast the xenomorphic extravaganza.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>We hope to convey to those not in the know what X-Com means to those that are. Utilizing the overlays and a fair dose of over-excitement, we feel like we are approaching a stream that is to at least our satisfaction, if not to that of the general gaming public.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Grubby – How’s the Weather?</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-hows-the-weather/</link><pubDate>Wed, 06 Jun 2012 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/esports/grubby-hows-the-weather/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/grubby_wallpaper_02.jpg">&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/grubby_wallpaper_02_thumb_3.png" alt="grubby_wallpaper_02" title="grubby_wallpaper_02">&lt;/a>
How’s the Weather Wallpaper - &lt;a href="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/recovered/grubby_wallpaper_02.jpg">Full size link&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It is finally finished.  I’ve been working for several months touch and go on this T-shirt concept for Starcraft 2 eSports Progamer, Manuel ‘Grubby’ Schenkhuizen.  I has been fun and challenging to create a fictional character that can summon lightening attacks at a whim.  There are many things I’d love to keep fixing up on the project, but I have to call it ‘done’ at some point.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Oh, it’s the Of..</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/oh-its-the-of/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Sep 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/art/illustration/oh-its-the-of/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;a href="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Oh-its-the-Of_C981/theofcover.jpg">&lt;img src="http://www.joshuakeyes.us/wordpress/raihn/images/Oh-its-the-Of_C981/theofcover_thumb.jpg" alt="theofcover" title="theofcover">&lt;/a>
Oh it’s the Of – Cover album artwork © 2011 Joshua Keyes&lt;/p>
